fusbar wrote:

>In bugs with a seat belt warning buzzer, there is a "key in ignition"
>switch.  This can be used to power a relay for the radio. Or so I've
>heard.  Do some Type2's have this buzzer?
>
>-fubar



75 has a buzzer but in 75 models it is "looking" for a ground. In this case 
you would need a relay.

It works without a relay in my 77 since the buzzer was "looking" for 12 
volts. I run my CD player directly off the the key buzzer wire left dangling 
by the PO(no relay needed).

